title: SIC! SIC! SIC!
html:
SIC! SIC! SIC!

“The mountain is named for the Rev. Starr King, who was an invertebrate climber.” [From The Boston Globe, 25 June 1984. Submitted by B. Goldstein, New Center, Massachusetts.]
